tafsir[8]{c,v,t}:
  15,74,"and We turned it uppermost nethermost and rained on it stones of baked clay."
  15,75,"Surely in that are signs for such as mark;"
  15,76,"surely it is on a way yet remaining;"
  15,77,"surely in that is a sign for believers."
  15,79,"and We took vengeance on them. The two of them were upon a roadway manifest."
  15,80,"The dwellers in El-Hijr cried lies to the Envoys."
  15,83,"and the Cry seized them in the morning;"
  15,84,"that they earned did not avail them."